'''可頌餅乾'''（{{lang-en|Rugelach}}；{{IPAc-en|ˈ|r|uː|ɡ|əl|ə|x}}；{{lang-yi|רוגעלך}}；{{lang-he|רוגלך}}）是一種猶太式[[糕點|糕點]]，由阿什肯納茲猶太人發明。它在以色列的咖啡廳及餅店很常見，也深受歐洲和美國的猶太人喜歡。

傳統的可頌餅乾形狀像牛角，用麵糰弄成三角形<ref name="Nathan">{{cite book |last= |first= |year=2004年 |author=Joan Nathan |title=Joan Nathan's Jewish Holiday Cookbook |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=38xF7g37ZT0C&pg=PA284 |location= |publisher=Schocken |page=284 |isbn= |author-link= |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303125532/https://books.google.com/books?id=38xF7g37ZT0C&pg=PA284 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Fertig">{{cite book |year=2003年 |author=Judith M. Fertig |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uioOx6UHZkcC&pg=PA134 |title=All American Desserts |publisher=Harvard Common Press |page=135 |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303131629/https://books.google.com/books?id=uioOx6UHZkcC&pg=PA134 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。有些文獻記載說可頌餅乾和法式牛角包一樣源於維也納<ref name="Marks">{{cite book |author=Gil Marks |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ux2lGKCKVPYC&pg=PA326 |title=The World of Jewish Cooking |publisher=Simon and Schuster |year=1996 |page=326 |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303130020/https://books.google.com/books?id=Ux2lGKCKVPYC&pg=PA326 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，因維也納之圍戰役而傳入。但這可能是都市傳説，可頌餅乾應在中世紀之後的近世出現，而法式牛角包在19世紀才出現。

另一種可頌餅乾呈卷狀，特別的是，它們在拿去焗之前會先切成一塊塊<ref>{{cite book |author=Joseph Amendola and Nicole Rees |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Yz0mF7pXZ38C&pg=223 |title=The Baker's Manual |publisher=Wiley |year=2003 |page=223 |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303125559/https://books.google.com/books?id=Yz0mF7pXZ38C&pg=223 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==詞源==
可頌餅乾這個名字源於[[意第緒語|意第緒語]]。“רוגעלך”的ך代表衆數；ל指小型的；רוגע意思是扭紋狀，整個字意思就是小型呈扭紋狀的餅乾。<ref name="Marks" /><ref>Alexander Harkavy, [https://books.google.com/books?id=dnMVAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA312 A Dictionary of the Yiddish Language] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dnMVAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA312 |date=20170303125745 }}, 1898; page 312.</ref>
在現代的希伯來文，可頌餅乾名叫“רוֹגְלִית”，就是尾隨藤的意思。<ref>{{cite book|author=Ernest Klein|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7bpiAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA609|title=A Comprehensive Etymological Dictionary of the Hebrew Language|publisher=McMillan|date=1987|page=609頁|access-date=2017-03-03|archive-date=2017-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305090844/https://books.google.com/books?id=7bpiAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA609|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==原料==
甜卷圈可以先由[[酸奶油|酸奶油]]或是[[奶油乳酪|奶油乳酪]]<ref name="Nathan" /><ref name="Fertig" /><ref name="Marks" />麵團製成，但也有由非奶製品作為原料的變化<ref name="Aish HaTorah">{{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=FU95wXi_L78C&pg=PA118 |title = The Taste of Shabbos |author = Aish HaTorah |year = 1987 |page = 118 |access-date = 2017-03-03 |archive-date = 2017-03-03 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170303131705/https://books.google.com/books?id=FU95wXi_L78C&pg=PA118 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。所以它可以搭配肉製品或在食用肉製品後食用，而且符合 [[猶太人紀律|猶太人紀律]]。 乳酪起司製成的麵糰是最近的，可能是美國的創新，餅乾餡料有很多種，例如葡萄乾、核桃、肉桂、巧克力、小杏仁餅，罌粟籽或水果等，包在餅乾中間。可頌餅乾類似於名叫Schneckenan的東歐猶太食品，使用奶油乳酪麵團及切成一片片。但可頌餅乾多爲三角形。近年來，可頌餅乾有了不同的變化，例如加入鷄肉或三文魚，變得出神入化。<ref name="Aish HaTorah" /><ref>{{cite book |author=Judy Bart Kancigor |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=c8YXwx08OFYC&pg=PA474 |title=Cooking Jewish |publisher=Workman |date=2007 |page=474 |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303125809/https://books.google.com/books?id=c8YXwx08OFYC&pg=PA474 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Barbara Grunes |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=juPycXQouOgC&pg=PA68 |title=The Best Bake Sale Ever Cookbook |publisher=Raincoast Books |location=Vancouver |date=2006 |page=68頁 |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303131850/https://books.google.com/books?id=juPycXQouOgC&pg=PA68 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Helene Siegel and Karen Gillingham |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i-YMAV8sYrkC&pg=PA74 |title=Totally Cookies Cookbook |publisher=Celestial Arts Publishing |year=1998 |page=74 |access-date=2017-03-03 |archive-date=2017-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303123527/https://books.google.com/books?id=i-YMAV8sYrkC&pg=PA74 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

